item.title: DENIED /usr/bin/sdwdate /usr/lib/sdwdate/sclockadj_debug_helper denied_mask="x"
item.dc:creator: Patrick
item.description:
We don’t have a flood of activity yet in this forum. And deterring posts by complicated rules seems wrong at this point. At some point we might need to switch to a pragmatic, “have rules” + “ignore the not-so-well written bug reports” + “work on well written bug reports” approach due to lack of time.

In my signature are some links (“HOT: How to Ask Smart Questions | How to Report Bugs Effectively”) that are supposed to explain how to write very good reports.

Read full topic
